<h2>You want security</h2>

<p>If you prefer to have a regular income you can use your pension pot to buy
  one. This is called an annuity. It’s a contract between you and an insurance
  company. You hand your pension pot over to them and they guarantee you regular
  payments until you die.</p>

<p>To calculate an annuity insurance companies take into account things like the
  size of your pot, your age and sometimes your health.</p>

<p>You can also buy an annuity that’s just for a fixed number of years instead of
  the rest of your life.</p>

<p>Once you’ve bought an annuity you can’t change it and usually you can’t pass
  it on to anyone after you die.</p>

<p>You pay tax on your annuity payments, just like you did on your salary.</p>

